51.6	Bradford	Bradford	Bradford lies at the heart of the City of Bradford, a metropolitan borough of West Yorkshire, in Northern England. It is situated in the foothills of the Pennines, 8.6 miles (13.8 km) west of Leeds, and 16 miles (25.7 km) northwest of Wakefield. Bradford became a municipal borough in 1847, and received its charter as a city in 1897. Following local government reform in 1974, city status was bestowed upon the wider metropolitan borough.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Bradford_Town_Hall.jpg/250px-Bradford_Town_Hall.jpg
